00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:12,639
But the folks who when I look at a resume and I see that someone's joined um they were at like really good companies when those companies were super exciting and in crazy growth mode.

211
00:16:12,639 --> 00:16:17,920
I'm like I instantly want to interview that candidate because I want to hear what they learned from being part of a winning team.

212
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:24,079
And that's um that's sort of one of my go-to heruristics when I'm looking at candidate profiles.

